          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2>Nature of Saju</h2>
        <p>
          Saju (Korean Four Pillars) is a traditional cultural practice with deep historical roots in Korean and East Asian philosophy. It is a system of interpretation based on cosmological principles and should be understood as a cultural traditionâ€”not as a scientifically validated method of prediction or analysis.
        </p>
        <p>
          We present Saju content as a way to explore Korean cultural heritage and as a tool for personal reflection. We do not claim that Saju can accurately predict the future or definitively determine personality traits.
        </p>

        <h2>Not Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>The content on this website is NOT and should NOT be considered as:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Medical Advice:</strong> Do not use Saju readings to diagnose, treat, or prevent any health conditions. Always consult qualified healthcare professionals for medical concerns.</li>
          <li><strong>Psychological Advice:</strong> Saju readings are not a substitute for professional mental health services. If you're experiencing psychological distress, please seek help from a licensed therapist or counselor.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Advice:</strong> Do not make legal decisions based on Saju content. Consult a qualified attorney for legal matters.</li>
          <li><strong>Financial Advice:</strong> Do not make investment or financial decisions based on Saju readings. Consult qualified financial advisors for money matters.</li>
          <li><strong>Relationship Counseling:</strong> Our compatibility tool is for entertainment only. For relationship issues, seek guidance from qualified relationship counselors.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>No Guarantees of Accuracy</h2>
        <p>
          We make no representations or warranties about the accuracy, reliability, completeness, or timeliness of any content on this Website. Our Saju calculations are based on traditional methods but may differ from other interpretations or practitioners.
        </p>

        <h2>Responsible Use</h2>
        <p>
          We encourage you to approach Saju with an open but critical mind. Use it as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A cultural learning experience</li>
          <li>A starting point for self-reflection</li>
          <li>An interesting way to explore personality concepts</li>
          <li>A fun activity to share with friends and family</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Do NOT use it as:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A definitive guide to your life path</li>
          <li>A basis for major life decisions</li>
          <li>A replacement for professional advice</li>
          <li>Evidence of predetermined destiny</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Beware of Scams</h2>
        <p>
          Unfortunately, some unethical practitioners may use Saju or similar practices to exploit vulnerable people. Be wary of anyone who:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Claims to know your exact future</li>
          <li>Pressures you to pay for "curse removal" or "luck enhancement"</li>
          <li>Uses fear-based language to encourage payment</li>
          <li>Makes absolute predictions about health, relationships, or finances</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Our tools are free to use, and we will never ask for payment to "fix" or "improve" your Saju.
